<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1669,1894]" pageId="14" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,1669,1695]" pageId="14" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. At present, defined only on the basis of characters that are symplesiomorphic with respect to 
<emphasis box="[151,309,1708,1733]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="48">Chimeromyia</emphasis>
: Arista terminal, with 
<number box="[576,590,1708,1734]" pageId="14" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
aristomeres; wing with crossveins r-m and bm-cu separated by distance approximately equal to length of r-m; cell dm present, large, with crossvein dm-cu; vein CuA 
<number box="[1268,1276,1763,1777]" pageId="14" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
, cell cu 
<emphasis box="[1370,1385,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="48">p</emphasis>
and A 
<number box="[172,180,1804,1818]" pageId="14" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
[+ CuA 
<number box="[269,277,1804,1818]" pageId="14" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
?] present; anal lobe and alula present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
